<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="advanced-adj">advanced <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əd'vɑːnst/    美 /əd'vænst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>先进的；高级的</strong></h4>
<p>very modern and highly developed：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Thanks to the advanced technology, we live in an age of bettered communication.
多亏了先进技术，我们生活在通讯更通畅的年代。</p><footer>2015 北京</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(课程) 高深的；高级的</strong></h4>
<p>(of a course of study) at a high or difficult level：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Oxford Advanced Learner’s Dictionary
《牛津高阶学习词典》</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was educated at Peking University, after which she went on to have her advanced study abroad.
她先在北京大学学习，然后出国深造。</p></div></div>